    "text": "Nature\u2019s paradise in Indonesia \u26f0\ud83c\udf3f   With its incredible diversity, cultural history and natural sights, it\u2019s no wonder that Indonesia is such a popular travel destination. Most people decide to visit for its impressive temples, adventurous beaches or blooming natural parks and unforgettable views like this - have you ever been? If not, is Indonesia on your bucketlist?  \ud83d\udccdPhotos and places in Indonesia: 1. Tumpak Sewu 2. Tegallalang 3. Tegallalang 4. Nusa Penida 5. Kelimutu National Park 6. Bromo Tengger Semeru 7. Wae Rebo Village 8. Broken Beach 9. Tumpak Sewu  \ud83c\uddee\ud83c\udde9 #discoverIndonesia with @malthezimakoff",
